---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Staircase Tiling Services — TILERSHUB Sri Lanka"
  description="Premium staircase tiling with double nosing, router edge finish, and skirting. Rs. 8,500 per step, all inclusive. TILERSHUB Sri Lanka."
  eyebrow="Staircase Tiling"
  heroTitle="Staircase Tiling<br /><em>Built to Impress</em>"
  heroSub="Every step finished to the highest standard — double nosing, router-profiled edges, side elevation tiling, and skirting all included in one fixed rate."
  badge="Rs. 8,500 / step"
/>

<!-- Overview -->
<section class="overview">
  <div class="ov-text">
    <div class="stag">The Service</div>
    <h2>Everything in<br />One Step Rate</h2>
    <p class="sdesc">
      Staircase tiling is one of the most visible features of any home — and one of
      the most demanding to execute. Rs. 8,500 per step covers the complete scope:
      tread, riser, nosing, router edge, side elevation, and skirting.
    </p>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li>Double nosing installation on every tread</li>
      <li>Router-profiled edge finish — clean, chip-resistant profile</li>
      <li>Full tread and riser tiling with level alignment</li>
      <li>Side elevation (string wall) tiling included</li>
      <li>Skirting along side wall included</li>
      <li>Swisstek grout throughout — stain-resistant joints</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="ov-price reveal">
    <div class="price-card">
      <div class="pc-label">Per Step — Complete</div>
      <div class="pc-price">Rs. 8,500</div>
      <div class="pc-unit">all inclusive</div>
      <div class="pc-note">Nosing · Router Edge · Tread · Riser · Side Elevation · Skirting</div>
    </div>
    <p class="price-note">Labour only. Client supplies tiles.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- What Makes a Step -->
<section class="anatomy">
  <div class="stag reveal">Step Breakdown</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Anatomy of a Finished Step</h2>
  <p class="sdesc reveal">
    Every element of the step is addressed — nothing is left as an exposed edge or
    raw cut.
  </p>
  <div class="parts-grid reveal">
    <div class="part">
      <div class="part-label">Tread</div>
      <div class="part-desc">The horizontal walking surface — tiled flat with full coverage and precise spacing to the nosing.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="part">
      <div class="part-label">Riser</div>
      <div class="part-desc">The vertical face between treads — tiled to match and aligned to grout lines of the tread above.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="part">
      <div class="part-label">Double Nosing</div>
      <div class="part-desc">Two-piece nosing caps the front edge of the tread, protecting it from chipping and providing a finished transition.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="part featured">
      <div class="part-label">Router Edge</div>
      <div class="part-desc">The nosing tile edge is machine-profiled with a router, creating a smooth curved or chamfered profile that is far superior to raw cut edges.</div>
      <div class="part-badge">Signature Finish</div>
    </div>
    <div class="part">
      <div class="part-label">Side Elevation</div>
      <div class="part-desc">The exposed side face of the staircase (the "string" wall) is tiled to complete the visual envelope of the staircase.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="part">
      <div class="part-label">Skirting</div>
      <div class="part-desc">Skirting tiles run along the wall adjacent to the staircase for a clean floor-to-wall transition at every step.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Process -->
<section class="process">
  <div class="stag reveal">How We Work</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Our Staircase Process</h2>
  <p class="sdesc reveal">Detailed work that rewards careful preparation at each stage.</p>
  <div class="steps reveal">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">01</div>
      <div class="step-name">Site Survey & Template</div>
      <div class="step-desc">We measure each step individually — no two staircases are exactly the same. Templates cut for nosing pieces.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">02</div>
      <div class="step-name">Surface Preparation</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Existing substrate cleaned and checked. Any damaged concrete steps repaired with patching compound before tiling begins.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">03</div>
      <div class="step-name">Nosing Fabrication</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Nosing pieces cut and router-profiled to match your chosen tile. Double-piece nosing assembled before installation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">04</div>
      <div class="step-name">Tread & Riser Installation</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Tiles set from the bottom step up — treads and risers aligned to maintain consistent grout joint lines throughout.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">05</div>
      <div class="step-name">Side Elevation & Skirting</div>
      <div class="step-desc">String wall tiled and skirting fitted. Corners mitred for a clean finish — no visible raw edges anywhere.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">06</div>
      <div class="step-name">Grouting & Polish</div>
      <div class="step-desc">Full grouting with Swisstek grout, grout haze removed, and a final polish to bring out the tile finish.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Why Router Edge -->
<section class="router">
  <div class="router-inner reveal">
    <div>
      <div class="stag">Why It Matters</div>
      <h2>The Router Edge<br />Difference</h2>
      <p class="sdesc">
        Most tilers simply polish-cut the nosing tile edge and leave it. We go further:
        every nosing edge is run through a router to create a smooth, professional
        profile that is safer underfoot, far more durable, and looks significantly
        better — especially on large-format tiles.
      </p>
      <div class="compare">
        <div class="compare-item bad">
          <div class="compare-label">Standard Cut Edge</div>
          <div class="compare-desc">Sharp, unfinished — chips easily, looks raw</div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-arrow">→</div>
        <div class="compare-item good">
          <div class="compare-label">TILERSHUB Router Edge</div>
          <div class="compare-desc">Smooth chamfered profile — durable, refined, safe</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq">
  <div class="stag reveal">FAQ</div>
  <h2 class="reveal">Common Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list reveal">
    <details class="faq-item" open>
      <summary>What exactly is included in the Rs. 8,500 per step rate?</summary>
      <p>Everything: tread tiling, riser tiling, double nosing installation, router edge profiling, side elevation tiling, and skirting. Labour and installation materials only — you supply the tiles.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can the same tile be used for tread and nosing?</summary>
      <p>Yes, and this is the most common approach. We cut the nosing pieces from the same tile and router-profile the edge. Alternatively, a contrasting nosing tile can be used for a two-tone effect.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How many steps can you complete per day?</summary>
      <p>Typically 10–14 steps per day depending on the staircase configuration, tile size, and whether the side elevation is complex.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you tile curved or spiral staircases?</summary>
      <p>Yes, curved staircases are possible. These require additional templating time and bespoke cuts — contact us for a custom quote.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What tile thickness works best for staircase nosing?</summary>
      <p>10mm tiles are standard. Thicker tiles (12mm+) provide a more substantial nosing profile. We advise against tiles thinner than 8mm for nosing applications due to chipping risk.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .overview {
    background: var(--off-white);
    padding: 5.5rem 4rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .check-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: .7rem;
    margin-top: .5rem;
  }

  .check-list li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: .75rem;
    font-size: .9rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .check-list li::before {
    content: '◆';
    font-size: .42rem;
    color: var(--clay);
    margin-top: .4rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .price-card {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 2rem 2.2rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pc-label {
    font-size: .65rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .12em;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,.45);
    margin-bottom: .5rem;
  }

  .pc-price {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--clay);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .pc-unit {
    font-size: .78rem;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,.4);
    margin-top: .25rem;
    margin-bottom: .8rem;
  }

  .pc-note {
    font-size: .78rem;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,.5);
    padding-top: .75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .price-note {
    font-size: .75rem;
    color: var(--warm-gray);
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* ── Anatomy ── */

  .anatomy {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    padding: 5.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .anatomy h2 { color: var(--cream); }
  .anatomy .sdesc { color: rgba(245,240,232,.45); }

  .parts-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .part {
    background: #211c18;
    border: 1.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,.06);
    padding: 1.8rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    position: relative;
    transition: border-color .25s;
  }

  .part:hover { border-color: rgba(196,120,74,.35); }

  .part.featured { border-color: var(--clay); }

  .part-label {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--cream);
    margin-bottom: .5rem;
  }

  .part-desc {
    font-size: .8rem;
    color: rgba(245,240,232,.4);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .part-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(196,120,74,.15);
    border: 1px solid rgba(196,120,74,.3);
    color: var(--clay);
    font-size: .6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: .06em;
    padding: .15rem .55rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    margin-top: .75rem;
  }

  /* ── Process ── */

  .process {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 5.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .step {
    padding: 1.8rem;
    background: var(--off-white);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--stone);
    border-radius: 3px;
    transition: border-color .2s;
  }

  .step:hover { border-color: var(--clay); }

  .step-num {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--stone);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: .7rem;
  }

  .step-name {
    font-size: .9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: .5rem;
  }

  .step-desc {
    font-size: .8rem;
    color: var(--warm-gray);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* ── Router Edge ── */

  .router {
    background: var(--sand);
    padding: 5.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .router-inner {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .compare {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .compare-item {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .compare-item.bad {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,.05);
    border: 1px solid var(--stone);
  }

  .compare-item.good {
    background: var(--charcoal);
    border: 1px solid var(--clay);
  }

  .compare-label {
    font-size: .78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: .3rem;
  }

  .compare-item.good .compare-label { color: var(--clay); }

  .compare-desc {
    font-size: .75rem;
    color: var(--warm-gray);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .compare-item.good .compare-desc { color: rgba(245,240,232,.5); }

  .compare-arrow {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--clay);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* ── FAQ ── */

  .faq {
    background: var(--off-white);
    padding: 5.5rem 4rem;
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 720px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: .6rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    background: var(--cream);
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--stone);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
    font-size: .9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .faq-item summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--clay);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }

  .faq-item p {
    padding: 0 1.4rem 1.1rem;
    font-size: .85rem;
    color: var(--warm-gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */

  @media (max-width: 1100px) {
    .overview, .anatomy, .process, .router, .faq {
      padding-left: 2.5rem;
      padding-right: 2.5rem;
    }

    .overview { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
    .parts-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
    .steps { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .overview, .anatomy, .process, .router, .faq {
      padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .parts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .compare { flex-direction: column; }
    .compare-arrow { transform: rotate(90deg); }
  }
</style>
